::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:48.140
<b>Whole Cake Island</b>

3
00:01:48.250 --> 00:01:50.580
<b>Adventure in the Mysterious Forest</b>

4
00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:50.080
Ready to launch!

5
00:01:50.710 --> 00:01:53.800
– I never get tired of looking at it!
– Me neither!

6
00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:56.470
Channel 3!

7
00:01:59.220 --> 00:02:00.720
Here it comes!

8
00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:03.560
Shark Submerge III !

9
00:02:13.510 --> 00:02:17.030
I'll take Pedro-san, then.

10
00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:19.190
I'm sorry, Luffy!

11
00:02:19.190 --> 00:02:24.120
I insisted on coming along,
but now I'm relying on Brook.

12
00:02:25.830 --> 00:02:31.670
I think I can help you, Pedro-san !
Infiltration is my specialty!

13
00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:36.000
I'll get a copy of the poneglyph at any cost!

14
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.380
Yeah, we'll be counting on you!
Brook! Pedro!

15
00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:43.510
Once we meet up with Sanji and Pudding,
we'll be waiting for you around here.

16
00:02:43.510 --> 00:02:49.350
We all have to be really careful!
Don't forget Pekoms' message!

17
00:02:49.350 --> 00:02:51.150
"Turn Back"

18
00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:55.650
Yeah, we decided to go on!
We just gotta do it!

19
00:02:55.650 --> 00:02:59.030
– We're counting on you!
– See you!

20
00:02:59.030 --> 00:03:00.200
Good luck!

21
00:03:00.890 --> 00:03:03.280
See you later!

22
00:03:03.280 --> 00:03:05.550
Okay, let's go!

23
00:03:40.810 --> 00:03:45.530
Depth: 15 meters. Visibility: good.

24
00:03:50.280 --> 00:03:52.170
It's going well!

25
00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:58.880
Let's go up the river,
straight to Big Mom's castle!

26
00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:01.460
I hope the river is deep.

27
00:04:01.460 --> 00:04:03.060
Thank you for this!

28
00:04:12.890 --> 00:04:16.400
<b>Southwest Coast</b>

29
00:04:16.400 --> 00:04:18.150
Yahoo!

30
00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:23.990
Okay, I landed!
We've arrived at Big Mom's island!

31
00:04:33.960 --> 00:04:36.920
– I smell an adventure!
– I don't want one!

32
00:04:36.920 --> 00:04:39.750
As soon as we find Sanji-kun,
we'll go back!

33
00:04:40.260 --> 00:04:45.170
Hey! Sanji! Pudding!

34
00:04:45.170 --> 00:04:48.680
We're here, as promised!

35
00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:51.600
Don't shout! The enemy will notice!

36
00:04:52.060 --> 00:04:55.980
Hey, did you really see them, Luffy?

37
00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:58.440
I did! I'm sure!

38
00:04:58.440 --> 00:05:02.570
But when we looked,
they were already gone!

39
00:05:04.030 --> 00:05:09.450
Yummy! Nami, try and eat the soil!
It's hard whipped cream!

40
00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:11.870
Yummy!

41
00:05:13.830 --> 00:05:18.790
You're right! It's meringue.
Is this island full of candies like the others?

42
00:05:18.790 --> 00:05:22.130
What?! I wanna live here!

43
00:05:23.940 --> 00:05:25.420
Around here!

44
00:05:26.340 --> 00:05:32.810
I'm sure I saw Sanji and Pudding here,
but when I looked away, they were gone!

45
00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:36.850
This is definitely the southwest coast.

46
00:05:36.850 --> 00:05:42.310
And you wouldn't lie about it,
but I don't know why they would leave.

47
00:05:42.310 --> 00:05:45.150
I wanna see Sanji already.

48
00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:50.240
Oh?

49
00:05:58.840 --> 00:05:59.630
Hey!

50
00:05:59.630 --> 00:06:01.370
There he is!

51
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:05.460
– Sanji!
– What?

52
00:06:12.350 --> 00:06:14.430
Sanji!

53
00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:16.430
– What happened?
– Hey!

54
00:06:17.520 --> 00:06:18.520
What's going on?

55
00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:22.610
Sanji was there just now!
Why is he hiding?

56
00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:24.480
Really?

57
00:06:34.780 --> 00:06:35.580
Oh?

58
00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:36.910
Sanji?

59
00:06:36.910 --> 00:06:39.670
What? Where did he go?

60
00:06:45.600 --> 00:06:49.640
We lost him!
But this place looks delicious!

61
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.730
It's a forest of sweets!

62
00:06:51.730 --> 00:06:53.600
It smells so good!

63
00:06:54.480 --> 00:06:58.100
If all three of them saw him,
it had to be him.

64
00:06:59.230 --> 00:07:02.860
But... why would he disappear?

65
00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:04.480
Sanji-kun...

66
00:07:05.110 --> 00:07:08.190
Believe this, if nothing else.

67
00:07:08.190 --> 00:07:12.200
I didn't mean to hide
anything from my friends.

68
00:07:12.570 --> 00:07:15.910
Maybe he feels embarrassed.

69
00:07:15.910 --> 00:07:21.170
Hey! Sanji! Come on out!

70
00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:24.380
We're here to pick you up!

71
00:07:24.380 --> 00:07:26.670
Sanji!

72
00:07:34.260 --> 00:07:36.810
Okay, let's split up and search!

73
00:07:36.810 --> 00:07:41.060
I'm going this way!
Where you see a bunch of cakes!

74
00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:42.710
I'm going straight!

75
00:07:42.710 --> 00:07:45.610
Where the sweet caramel-like
smell is coming from!

76
00:07:45.610 --> 00:07:50.780
Then, I'll go this way!
Look at those beautiful jellybeans!

77
00:07:50.780 --> 00:07:54.320
Wait! I don't want a secondary disaster!

78
00:07:54.320 --> 00:07:58.920
What?! We just lost him,
so all we can do is follow our gut.

79
00:07:58.920 --> 00:08:01.540
That's how people who get lost would think.

80
00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:06.080
Plus, aren't you guys being motivated 
by some other cravings?!

81
00:08:07.020 --> 00:08:09.090
Some other?

82
00:08:10.300 --> 00:08:12.470
No, we aren't.

83
00:08:13.060 --> 00:08:14.840
Don't lie!

84
00:08:14.840 --> 00:08:22.060
All right! I'll search with you guys!
All three of you, stay with me! Okay?

85
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:23.890
Mm-hm. Got it!

86
00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:31.690
– This flower is candy!
– Really?!

87
00:08:31.690 --> 00:08:34.900
This is where the caramel smell comes from!

88
00:08:41.370 --> 00:08:45.690
It's so sweet! It sticks to my teeth!

89
00:08:45.690 --> 00:08:48.430
I'm so happy!

90
00:08:53.800 --> 00:09:00.060
Hey, guys! Do you remember?
We're here to pick up Sanji-kun !

91
00:09:00.060 --> 00:09:03.060
You guys are too distracted by the candy!

92
00:09:03.060 --> 00:09:05.310
I thought we were gonna look for Sanji-kun !

93
00:09:05.310 --> 00:09:07.150
I know!

94
00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:10.610
But there are sweets everywhere!

95
00:09:10.610 --> 00:09:15.450
Don't you think that's strange?!
We're in the enemy's territory!

96
00:09:15.450 --> 00:09:19.790
We'll search to some extent,
and if we can't find him, we'll go back.

97
00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:21.410
What?!

98
00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:22.950
Why?!

99
00:09:27.310 --> 00:09:30.130
This green river! It's melon juice!

100
00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:32.090
Really?! Let me try!

101
00:09:32.090 --> 00:09:35.340
If you take a close look at this bridge,
it's a donut!

102
00:09:35.340 --> 00:09:38.090
Hey! That's enough!

103
00:09:45.810 --> 00:09:47.140
Cross the bridge!

104
00:09:52.520 --> 00:09:53.610
Nami!

105
00:10:05.580 --> 00:10:07.020
It's a crocodile!

106
00:10:08.120 --> 00:10:10.250
Do you wanna take it down, Luffy?!

107
00:10:13.080 --> 00:10:14.050
No.

108
00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:21.260
Oh, just humans.

109
00:10:31.650 --> 00:10:33.690
What did you think we were?!

110
00:10:33.690 --> 00:10:34.980
That's not important!

111
00:10:34.980 --> 00:10:38.650
The crocodile is wearing clothes and a hat
and he talked!

112
00:10:38.650 --> 00:10:41.700
Just as I thought,
this forest is dangerous and strange!

113
00:10:42.610 --> 00:10:46.080
If that surprises you, take a look at us.

114
00:10:47.810 --> 00:10:51.170
Well, I know what you mean, but...

115
00:11:06.140 --> 00:11:10.180
I think we'd better trust Pudding
and wait by the sea!

116
00:11:10.180 --> 00:11:12.850
I'm sure she'll bring Sanji-kun !

117
00:11:12.850 --> 00:11:16.150
And look!
Our road back is already problematic!

118
00:11:16.150 --> 00:11:19.900
We'll be fine. If we jump over
the river, we can always go back.

119
00:11:22.490 --> 00:11:24.660
What?

120
00:11:25.080 --> 00:11:26.700
What?

121
00:11:34.330 --> 00:11:35.420
What?!

122
00:11:35.420 --> 00:11:39.130
There's another Luffy?!

123
00:11:39.130 --> 00:11:41.130
What?!

124
00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:42.880
– Who are you?!
– Who are you?!

125
00:11:48.520 --> 00:11:52.810
– "Who are you?!" I'm Luffy! Stop mocking me!
– "Who are you?!" I'm Luffy! Stop mocking me!

126
00:11:52.810 --> 00:11:55.400
What's going on?!
Which one is the real Luffy?!

127
00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:58.530
They move and talk exactly the same!

128
00:11:58.530 --> 00:12:00.490
No, they're a bit different!

129
00:12:05.410 --> 00:12:12.040
Like a mirror image, his scar and accessories
and everything are inverted.

130
00:12:12.860 --> 00:12:16.590
It really looks like there's a mirror!
Who is that?!

131
00:12:16.590 --> 00:12:19.130
Who are you?!

132
00:12:19.130 --> 00:12:23.050
– She's asking who you are! Answer her, you idiot!
– She's asking who you are! Answer her, you idiot!

133
00:12:25.890 --> 00:12:28.260
There he is! I found Sanji!

134
00:12:28.970 --> 00:12:31.060
There! Up in the tree!

135
00:12:33.560 --> 00:12:36.270
Hey! Sanji!

136
00:12:39.270 --> 00:12:41.490
Get out of my way, you fool!

137
00:12:41.490 --> 00:12:44.570
Sanji-kun, what are you doing up there?!

138
00:12:45.240 --> 00:12:48.620
Oh, he's running again! Sanji!

139
00:12:49.870 --> 00:12:54.200
You bastard! Outta my way!

140
00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:02.760
Damn! You guys, go ahead!
Chase him!

141
00:13:02.760 --> 00:13:04.200
O-Okay!

142
00:13:04.200 --> 00:13:05.760
I'm coming too!

143
00:13:05.760 --> 00:13:08.730
Don't get separated!
Chopper! Carrot!

144
00:13:08.730 --> 00:13:12.680
This forest is strange!
Something's gonna happen again!

145
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:15.980
I know! But if we lose Sanji again...

146
00:13:15.980 --> 00:13:18.110
Sanji!

147
00:13:18.110 --> 00:13:20.150
Nami, go with them!

148
00:13:20.150 --> 00:13:22.480
I'll catch up with you after I beat him up!

149
00:13:22.480 --> 00:13:24.450
Yeah, okay!

150
00:13:31.740 --> 00:13:35.710
Sanji!

151
00:13:56.560 --> 00:13:59.020
Gum-Gum...

152
00:13:59.020 --> 00:14:01.860
Gatling!

153
00:14:10.160 --> 00:14:13.700
Who the hell are you?!

154
00:14:31.460 --> 00:14:32.550
What?!

155
00:14:38.370 --> 00:14:42.670
Th-There's a humongous half-buried man!

156
00:14:42.670 --> 00:14:44.540
It's a giant!

157
00:14:46.190 --> 00:14:49.780
– You scared me!
– We should be saying that!

158
00:14:49.780 --> 00:14:53.800
Are you okay?!
Who did this to you?!

159
00:14:53.800 --> 00:14:54.950
What?

160
00:14:54.950 --> 00:14:58.120
Your body is half buried!

161
00:14:58.580 --> 00:15:02.130
I'm half buried because I want to be.

162
00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:05.880
What?! Is he stupid?!
I shouldn't have been worried!

163
00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:08.260
The thing is...

164
00:15:09.720 --> 00:15:11.190
I wanna have some juice.

165
00:15:11.190 --> 00:15:12.680
I don't care!

166
00:15:14.550 --> 00:15:19.390
Chopper, don't take him seriously!
He'll drive you crazy!

167
00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:23.270
Wait, wait, you guys.

168
00:15:23.270 --> 00:15:25.230
He's saying something.

169
00:15:25.230 --> 00:15:26.730
Ignore him!

170
00:15:27.870 --> 00:15:31.450
I like apple juice very much.

171
00:15:31.450 --> 00:15:34.120
– So what?!
– Don't listen to him.

172
00:15:34.120 --> 00:15:39.770
If you go left,
there are waterfalls of apple juice.

173
00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:42.330
I like them very much.

174
00:15:42.330 --> 00:15:46.890
Remember what Luffy told us?
We should be looking for Sanji-kun.

175
00:15:48.480 --> 00:15:51.260
Am I dreaming?

176
00:15:51.940 --> 00:15:55.970
You're looking for someone, aren't you?
He came this way.

177
00:15:55.970 --> 00:15:58.220
What?! Did he?!

178
00:15:58.220 --> 00:16:01.810
I said, "Don't take him seriously!"

179
00:16:01.810 --> 00:16:06.400
If you get me some apple juice,
I'll tell you.

180
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:07.860
Okay, okay.

181
00:16:11.490 --> 00:16:14.030
Watch out! Nami! Chopper!

182
00:16:31.200 --> 00:16:32.130
A rabbit?!

183
00:16:35.430 --> 00:16:37.100
No! Let's run!

184
00:16:59.110 --> 00:17:05.250
There are talking trees and crocodiles,
and the rabbit was trying to kill us!

185
00:17:05.250 --> 00:17:09.280
This place is weird.
Let's go back to see Luffy!

186
00:17:09.280 --> 00:17:12.090
We still know the way!

187
00:17:12.090 --> 00:17:14.070
But, what about Sanji?!

188
00:17:14.070 --> 00:17:17.310
We don't know
if he was real or not anymore!

189
00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:21.720
We finally saw each other,
but he didn't even get up!

190
00:17:21.720 --> 00:17:24.110
He didn't say anything!

191
00:17:25.010 --> 00:17:26.270
Yeah...

192
00:17:26.270 --> 00:17:29.360
And if that's the real Sanji-kun,

193
00:17:29.360 --> 00:17:32.610
do you think he'd just stand by
and watch us going through this?!

194
00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:34.940
All right. Let's go back.

195
00:17:36.740 --> 00:17:38.840
The needles are...

196
00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:41.740
Look! The clock is like that, too!

197
00:17:48.170 --> 00:17:51.210
Everything about this forest is strange!

198
00:18:17.030 --> 00:18:18.640
♪ Did you hear that? ♪

199
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:20.280
♪ Yes, I did! ♪

200
00:18:20.280 --> 00:18:23.580
♪ Move over! ♪

201
00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:26.780
♪ Tree, tree, tree, tree! ♪

202
00:18:23.610 --> 00:18:30.210
<b>Whole Cake Island's Southwest Coast</b>

203
00:18:26.780 --> 00:18:30.210
♪ Close up their way out! ♪

204
00:18:30.210 --> 00:18:36.590
♪ Flower! Flower! Flower! ♪

205
00:18:36.590 --> 00:18:39.680
♪ Let's play! ♪

206
00:18:39.680 --> 00:18:43.060
♪ Let's play a murder game! ♪

207
00:18:47.430 --> 00:18:51.650
– Chopper, can't you go faster?!
– This is the fastest I can go!

208
00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:53.150
Is he coming?

209
00:18:53.150 --> 00:18:55.650
Yeah, he's coming after us!

210
00:18:55.650 --> 00:18:58.180
We gotta get out of this
forest as soon as possible!

211
00:18:58.180 --> 00:18:58.820
Yeah!

212
00:18:58.820 --> 00:19:01.320
That rabbit is formidable!

213
00:19:03.780 --> 00:19:06.160
But he's not a mink!

214
00:19:06.160 --> 00:19:07.220
Are you sure?!

215
00:19:07.220 --> 00:19:08.500
Did he eat a devil fruit?

216
00:19:11.830 --> 00:19:12.960
♪ They've noticed! ♪

217
00:19:12.960 --> 00:19:18.170
♪ The Straw Hats have noticed! ♪

218
00:19:18.170 --> 00:19:20.010
♪ Us! ♪

219
00:19:20.010 --> 00:19:23.220
♪ – No, they haven't
– There's something wrong! ♪

220
00:19:23.220 --> 00:19:24.640
♪ They've noticed! ♪

221
00:19:24.640 --> 00:19:27.970
♪ – Madame Brûlée is...
– ...playing with them! ♪

222
00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:30.900
♪ Whose prey are they? ♪

223
00:19:30.900 --> 00:19:37.610
♪ It would be delicious if we were to 
make smoothies out of them! ♪

224
00:20:03.130 --> 00:20:05.550
See! He can't use Electro!

225
00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:08.610
Take this!

226
00:20:09.600 --> 00:20:12.520
– Carrot! Stay with us!
– Okay!

227
00:20:12.520 --> 00:20:14.270
I'm sorry, Bird-san !

228
00:20:15.030 --> 00:20:15.690
C...

229
00:20:15.690 --> 00:20:18.110
Crane!

230
00:20:18.230 --> 00:20:22.610
<b>"Crane Rider" Randolph
Big Mom Pirates</b>

231
00:20:30.610 --> 00:20:32.750
– The weapon is...
– ...coming toward us!

232
00:20:47.870 --> 00:20:51.810
Big Mom's castle, Whole Cake Chateau.

233
00:20:52.230 --> 00:20:56.190
The lake behind it is called Lake Aprico.

234
00:21:04.400 --> 00:21:08.370
This is Germa's ship!
Requesting permission to enter the port!

235
00:21:08.370 --> 00:21:10.710
Go ahead!

236
00:21:12.040 --> 00:21:15.420
Only the ships of Big Mom's subordinates

237
00:21:15.420 --> 00:21:20.210
or those soon to join her empire, are allowed entry.

238
00:21:20.210 --> 00:21:22.920
Keep it coming! Keep it coming!

239
00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:38.480
Keep it coming! Keep it coming!

240
00:21:38.480 --> 00:21:41.400
All right. Stop right there!

241
00:21:41.400 --> 00:21:43.870
Brace for the impact!

242
00:21:52.510 --> 00:21:54.250
Germa is

243
00:21:54.250 --> 00:21:59.840
the name of the one and only seafaring kingdom
that has no land of its own.

244
00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:03.120
Several dozen of their ships
 travel independently,

245
00:22:03.120 --> 00:22:07.930
but occasionally come together
to form the shape of the kingdom.

246
00:22:17.520 --> 00:22:21.650
The country is ruled by the
Vinsmoke family,

247
00:22:21.650 --> 00:22:24.870
which once conquered the North Blue by force.

248
00:22:24.870 --> 00:22:27.940
This is the Kingdom of Germa.

249
00:22:27.940 --> 00:22:33.500
Their army, Germa 66,
is still viewed as a threat in the world.

250
00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:38.120
Most of its citizens are men and soldiers.

251
00:22:48.300 --> 00:22:52.970
There is not a day that
they don't train themselves.

252
00:23:07.070 --> 00:23:10.000
Why don't you go away already?

253
00:23:10.910 --> 00:23:13.370
How could you say that...

254
00:23:13.370 --> 00:23:16.240
to your sister who you haven't seen
for 13 years?

255
00:23:21.670 --> 00:23:23.750
How many times do I have to tell you?

256
00:23:23.750 --> 00:23:27.960
I cut ties with you guys
under no uncertain terms!

257
00:23:27.960 --> 00:23:32.470
You guys must be crazy
to put up a tasteless picture like this!

258
00:23:46.400 --> 00:23:50.850
The big incident where four kings in the North Blue
were put down.

259
00:23:50.850 --> 00:23:52.920
The Conquest of Four Nations.

260
00:23:54.280 --> 00:24:00.420
Our father's dream is to bring the North Blue
under Germa's control again.

261
00:24:01.120 --> 00:24:02.680
What's wrong with that?

262
00:24:02.680 --> 00:24:06.290
It's natural for men to seek power and fame.

263
00:24:07.120 --> 00:24:10.670
Why don't you enjoy being a
member of privileged royalty

264
00:24:10.670 --> 00:24:14.270
rather than staying in a
silly little pirate group?

265
00:24:14.800 --> 00:24:16.510
Screw you.

266
00:24:16.510 --> 00:24:21.850
Look. These 10 waiting maids
will do whatever you ask them to.

267
00:24:21.850 --> 00:24:24.810
Don't hesitate to ask, Your Highness.

268
00:24:25.980 --> 00:24:27.270
Nice, nice!

269
00:24:27.270 --> 00:24:29.860
That's because you're of royal blood.

270
00:24:29.860 --> 00:24:35.780
If we keep sending our troops to countries in war,
we'll never run out of money.

271
00:24:35.780 --> 00:24:38.280
You won't have to fight at all.

272
00:24:39.570 --> 00:24:41.500
Don't you like the sound of that?

273
00:24:42.930 --> 00:24:49.060
We Vinsmokes have always gained
wealth through our force of arms.

274
00:24:50.670 --> 00:24:53.410
You have that blood in your veins.

275
00:24:53.410 --> 00:24:55.260
Like I care.

276
00:24:55.260 --> 00:24:57.210
I'm not gonna marry her!

277
00:24:57.210 --> 00:25:00.560
Pudding is a nice girl, isn't she?
I like her.

278
00:25:02.140 --> 00:25:04.140
Generalissimo, where are you going?

279
00:25:04.140 --> 00:25:06.270
I'm gonna go see Sanji.

280
00:25:06.270 --> 00:25:07.770
Don't bother me.

281
00:25:21.240 --> 00:25:24.040
Esteemed Father, why are you here?

282
00:25:26.040 --> 00:25:31.670
<b>Vinsmoke Judge
King of Germa and Generalissimo of Germa 66</b>

283
00:25:31.670 --> 00:25:33.880
Are you still whining?

284
00:25:34.470 --> 00:25:36.300
You bastard...

285
00:25:41.600 --> 00:25:43.890
Oh, my son.

286
00:25:43.890 --> 00:25:45.690
Don't call me that.

287
00:25:45.690 --> 00:25:49.270
Even if I call someone "Father",
it wouldn't be you!

288
00:25:53.620 --> 00:25:58.910
Did you do something to Yonji?
He is quite strong.

289
00:25:58.910 --> 00:26:01.370
I guess I'm stronger than him!

290
00:26:08.670 --> 00:26:11.340
Step outside!

291
00:26:12.600 --> 00:26:15.920
Men should talk with their fists.

292
00:26:20.680 --> 00:26:23.850
<b>The Seducing Woods</b>

293
00:26:24.770 --> 00:26:27.140
Chopper! Carrot! Dodge!

294
00:26:27.140 --> 00:26:28.230
Okay!

295
00:26:31.150 --> 00:26:34.180
What's going on back there...?

296
00:26:34.180 --> 00:26:36.220
No!

297
00:26:37.200 --> 00:26:38.240
What?!

298
00:26:38.240 --> 00:26:40.660
He can serve as a landmark!

299
00:26:40.660 --> 00:26:44.830
Oh, you guys from earlier!

300
00:26:50.740 --> 00:26:52.710
The field of lollipops!

301
00:26:52.710 --> 00:26:56.170
A little more to go until we reach Luffy!

302
00:26:57.510 --> 00:27:01.010
You bastard! Outta my way!

303
00:27:05.810 --> 00:27:08.770
– He's still fighting!
– Luffy!

304
00:27:08.770 --> 00:27:10.980
Let's go back to the coast!

305
00:27:11.420 --> 00:27:13.980
Oh? Why're you guys here?!

306
00:27:13.980 --> 00:27:16.780
Hurry up! I'll tell you later!

307
00:27:16.780 --> 00:27:19.360
This forest has a bunch of creepy traps!

308
00:27:19.860 --> 00:27:21.360
Okay!

309
00:27:23.370 --> 00:27:25.000
Somebody's after us!

310
00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:27.200
Let's get out of the
forest as fast as we can!

311
00:27:35.710 --> 00:27:38.670
That's the river where
we saw the talking crocodile!

312
00:27:38.670 --> 00:27:42.700
If I remember right, as soon as we
cross the river, we can get out!

313
00:27:42.700 --> 00:27:45.430
Let's jump over it like this!

314
00:27:45.430 --> 00:27:48.140
Here we go!

315
00:27:50.020 --> 00:27:53.980
Wait, guys! That's not the real m–

316
00:27:53.980 --> 00:27:56.190
Did you say something, Luffy?!

317
00:27:56.190 --> 00:27:57.360
No, I didn't.

318
00:28:01.360 --> 00:28:05.200
Guys! Let's keep running
without slowing down!

319
00:28:05.200 --> 00:28:06.330
Okay!

320
00:28:07.210 --> 00:28:08.620
What happened to Sanji?!

321
00:28:08.620 --> 00:28:13.060
He ran away from us
and didn't come back!

322
00:28:13.060 --> 00:28:17.630
Something's wrong with him,
even though he sure looks like Sanji!

323
00:28:17.630 --> 00:28:20.090
Let's talk after we get out, Nami!

324
00:28:20.090 --> 00:28:23.130
Yeah! I'm glad that we still know the way!

325
00:28:23.630 --> 00:28:25.680
We'll reach the coast soon!

326
00:28:25.680 --> 00:28:26.680
Yeah!

327
00:28:30.430 --> 00:28:31.180
Oh?!

328
00:28:31.180 --> 00:28:33.350
– Huh?
– What?

329
00:28:39.230 --> 00:28:42.610
What?! Why?!

330
00:28:42.610 --> 00:28:46.070
Oh, it's you guys again!

331
00:28:46.070 --> 00:28:49.330
Hey, could you pull out the thing
that's stuck to my...

332
00:28:49.330 --> 00:28:53.500
We just went straight back the way we came!

333
00:28:53.500 --> 00:28:56.580
Why are you here?!

334
00:28:57.360 --> 00:29:01.300
Don't yell. It scares me.

335
00:29:01.300 --> 00:29:08.010
Did you ask why I'm here?
I was here the whole time!

336
00:29:08.010 --> 00:29:13.820
It's you guys that left and came back.

337
00:29:13.820 --> 00:29:16.940
– Chopper, let's try again!
– Uh-huh!

338
00:29:17.810 --> 00:29:21.730
Hey! Pull out the thing
that's stuck in my head!

339
00:29:26.200 --> 00:29:28.570
Running through the field of lollipops...

340
00:29:34.580 --> 00:29:36.620
Jumping over the crocodile's river...

341
00:29:40.420 --> 00:29:42.510
Let's get to the coast this time!

342
00:29:47.590 --> 00:29:49.510
You scared me!

343
00:29:50.010 --> 00:29:52.810
Why do you guys keep coming back here?

344
00:29:52.810 --> 00:29:57.900
Again?! Even without the log pose working,

345
00:29:57.900 --> 00:30:02.070
we don't need to know the directions,
because it's one simple path!

346
00:30:04.660 --> 00:30:06.650
Going straight back this way...

347
00:30:06.650 --> 00:30:10.280
Slowly... Slowly...

348
00:30:12.480 --> 00:30:13.410
Oops.

349
00:30:13.880 --> 00:30:15.250
Flower?!

350
00:30:15.250 --> 00:30:18.120
What?! The trees and flowers are moving!

351
00:30:18.120 --> 00:30:20.750
One, two! One, two!

352
00:30:20.750 --> 00:30:23.420
The soil is moving and talking!

353
00:30:24.170 --> 00:30:25.420
What's going on?

354
00:30:25.420 --> 00:30:28.720
What are those things?
What's with this forest?!

355
00:30:28.720 --> 00:30:31.970
– They found out!
– They did!

356
00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:35.720
♪ Flower! ♪

357
00:30:35.720 --> 00:30:39.480
There was no path from the beginning!

358
00:30:40.310 --> 00:30:43.400
You finally became aware...

359
00:30:43.400 --> 00:30:45.800
of the terror of this forest!

360
00:30:45.800 --> 00:30:48.240
Hey, Luffy, what are you doing?!

361
00:30:48.800 --> 00:30:52.660
This is the Seducing Woods!

362
00:30:52.660 --> 00:30:54.870
Nami! That's not Luffy!

363
00:31:06.420 --> 00:31:08.380
Who are you?!

364
00:31:08.800 --> 00:31:10.640
Who am I?

365
00:31:14.420 --> 00:31:18.060
We were together the whole time!

366
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:23.650
No matter how many times you try,
you'll never get out of this forest!

367
00:31:24.920 --> 00:31:26.790
Never...

368
00:31:26.790 --> 00:31:29.320
Not until you die!

369
00:31:29.320 --> 00:31:31.480
Let go of me!

370
00:31:31.480 --> 00:31:35.480
Calm down, young girl.

371
00:31:35.480 --> 00:31:39.620
Look at the scar on my face.

372
00:31:36.230 --> 00:31:41.210
<b>Charlotte Brûlée
8th Daughter of the Charlotte Family</b>

373
00:31:39.620 --> 00:31:41.210
Isn't it terrible?

374
00:31:41.210 --> 00:31:43.670
Who are you?! A tree?

375
00:31:43.670 --> 00:31:47.050
I'm not a damn tree! I'm Brûlée!

376
00:31:47.050 --> 00:31:48.650
Brûlée?

377
00:31:48.650 --> 00:31:53.720
A cute rabbit... and a pretty girl...

378
00:31:53.720 --> 00:32:00.180
How nice...
When I see your beautiful faces...

379
00:32:01.730 --> 00:32:05.310
it makes me want to scratch them up!
